00:32:28.740 --> 00:32:30.610
你喜歡什麼樣的 昆特
What is your type, Günther?


359
00:32:30.620 --> 00:32:33.200
你這樣的 伊娜 你是知道的
You are, Irna. You know that.


360
00:33:01.300 --> 00:33:03.640
去約翰內斯•勃拉姆斯廣場
Johannes-Brahms-Platz.


361
00:33:15.100 --> 00:33:17.120
你好 湯姆
Hello, Tommy.


362
00:33:20.700 --> 00:33:22.240
你是誰
And you are?


363
00:33:22.460 --> 00:33:24.760
我叫巴克曼
My name is Bachmann.


364
00:33:25.660 --> 00:33:28.280
領導一個反恐小組
I head an anti-terror unit


365
00:33:28.740 --> 00:33:33.480
知道我們的人不多 喜歡我們的更少
not many people know about and even less like.


366
00:33:56.100 --> 00:33:58.090
我們走走
Let's walk.


367
00:34:14.420 --> 00:34:17.850
漢堡是世上最偉大的港口之一 湯姆
Hamburg is one of the great ports of the world, Tommy.


368
00:34:17.860 --> 00:34:20.330
數百年來 它張開雙臂
For centuries it opened its arms


369
00:34:20.340 --> 00:34:24.040
歡迎被沖上海岸的每一個外國人
to every foreigner who washed up on its shores.


370
00:34:24.940 --> 00:34:27.210
而如今在911之後
Now, since 9/11,


371
00:34:27.220 --> 00:34:29.450
每個深色皮膚的人
in the eyes of every dark-skinned man


372
00:34:29.460 --> 00:34:32.050
我們都感覺這些人可能會殺害我們
we see someone who wants to kill us.


373
00:34:32.060 --> 00:34:34.280
而且 確實有此可能
Problem is some of them do,


374
00:34:34.420 --> 00:34:38.810
問題是 伊薩•卡爾波夫是不是這樣的人
but the question is whether Issa Karpov is one of them.


375
00:34:40.500 --> 00:34:42.520
那個律師
The lawyer.


376
00:34:43.500 --> 00:34:44.810
律師？
Lawyer?


377
00:34:44.820 --> 00:34:46.890
安娜貝爾•裡克特
Annabel Richter.


378
00:34:47.340 --> 00:34:50.410
你在酒店見過的律師  想和她上床的那個律師
The one you met at the hotel. The one you'd like to fuck.


379
00:34:50.780 --> 00:34:52.850
怎麼 難道不是嗎
What? Not true?


380
00:34:52.900 --> 00:34:55.450
你對她來說太老了 你我都太老了
You're too old for her, Tommy. We both are.


381
00:34:55.460 --> 00:34:58.330
見到她 愛上她 但你永遠得不到她
See her, love her, but you'll never get her,


382
00:34:58.340 --> 00:35:00.210
即使有那一筆
not even with all that black money


383
00:35:00.220 --> 00:35:02.490
藏在你銀行金庫的黑錢
you've got tucked away in your bank vaults.


384
00:35:02.500 --> 00:35:06.250
我只知道裡克特小姐代表的客戶
As far as I am aware, Miss Richter represents


385
00:35:06.260 --> 00:35:11.490
在我的銀行裡有合法的金融業務
a client with a legitimate financial interest with my bank.


386
00:35:11.500 --> 00:35:14.450
你的銀行與俄國人做生意吧
Your bank does business with the Russians, right?


387
00:35:14.460 --> 00:35:17.090
以前是的 在我父親的時代
It did. In my father's time.


388
00:35:17.100 --> 00:35:18.600
黑手黨？
Mafia?


389
00:35:18.700 --> 00:35:20.800
主要是軍方的
Military mainly.


390
00:35:22.980 --> 00:35:26.090
我完全可以
What's to stop me


391
00:35:26.100 --> 00:35:29.640
對此置身事外
from just walking away from this?


392
00:35:30.260 --> 00:35:32.610
不管是什麼渾水
Whatever this is.


393
00:35:32.620 --> 00:35:36.400
要不要先全面審計一下你的帳目？
How about we start with a full audit of your books?


394
00:35:37.580 --> 00:35:42.290
你父親並非只是個銀行家 湯姆
But your father wasn't just a banker, Tommy.


395
00:35:42.340 --> 00:35:43.730
還從事洗錢
He was a laundryman.


396
00:35:43.740 --> 00:35:44.770
你是在威脅我？
You're threatening me?


397
00:35:44.780 --> 00:35:46.480
只是同情你
Just sympathizing.


398
00:35:47.140 --> 00:35:49.640
留給你收拾殘局
You've been left to clean up the mess.


399
00:36:07.140 --> 00:36:09.880
我們有工作要做 湯姆
We have a job to do, Tommy.


400
00:36:10.860 --> 00:36:12.570
你要協助我們
You're going to help me do it.


401
00:36:12.580 --> 00:36:14.730
到底做什麼
Do what exactly?


402
00:36:14.740 --> 00:36:17.690
先從挽救安娜貝爾•裡克特開始
Save Annabel Richter, for a start.


403
00:36:17.700 --> 00:36:19.530
為了什麼
From what?


404
00:36:21.020 --> 00:36:23.320
為所有的事情
From all of it.


405
00:36:55.820 --> 00:36:57.770
沒想到你會來
Hmm. I wasn't expecting you.


406
00:36:57.780 --> 00:36:59.090
是嗎
No?


407
00:36:59.100 --> 00:37:01.520
你以為誰會來
Who were you expecting?


408
00:37:02.540 --> 00:37:04.240
今天不順心？
Bad day?


409
00:37:04.580 --> 00:37:06.730
發生了一些意外
A few surprises.


410
00:37:12.740 --> 00:37:15.360
享用你的威士忌 湯姆
Enjoy your scotch, Tommy.


411
00:37:16.340 --> 00:37:19.760
上床時儘量別摔倒了
And try not to fall over on your way to bed.


412
00:38:08.940 --> 00:38:11.640
伊薩 有人來找你
Issa, it is somebody for you.


413
00:38:15.340 --> 00:38:17.170
-旱上好  -早上好
- Good morning. - Good morning.


414
00:38:17.180 --> 00:38:18.250
謝謝你前來
Thank you for coming.


415
00:38:18.260 --> 00:38:19.370
不客氣
Of course.


416
00:38:21.100 --> 00:38:22.680
伊薩
Issa.


417
00:38:23.420 --> 00:38:25.160
這位是布魯先生
This is Mr. Brue.


418
00:38:25.700 --> 00:38:27.440
早上好
Morning.


419
00:38:29.500 --> 00:38:32.480
你可以讓他看看信
Perhaps you could show him the letter.


420
00:38:37.540 --> 00:38:39.760
親愛的卡爾波夫：
"My dear Karpov,


421
00:38:40.300 --> 00:38:42.690
正如我們討論過的 請接收這封信
"as discussed, please accept this letter


422
00:38:42.700 --> 00:38:45.890
做為一個朋友對另一個朋友的擔保
"as assurance from one friend to another,


423
00:38:45.900 --> 00:38:49.010
假如你不幸去世
"that in the unfortunate circumstance of your death


424
00:38:49.020 --> 00:38:52.730
我會很高興把你的兒子
"I should be pleased to acquaint your own dear son,


425
00:38:52.740 --> 00:38:54.650
伊萬•格裡維奇•卡爾波夫
"Ivan Grigorevich Karpov,


426
00:38:54.660 --> 00:38:58.200
介紹給我們的朋友"利比紮馬"
"with our friend Mr. Lipizzaner.


427
00:38:58.500 --> 00:39:00.090
他只需要持有這封信
"He need only present this letter,


428
00:39:00.100 --> 00:39:02.130
再帶上你的器具
"together with the necessary instrument


429
00:39:02.140 --> 00:39:05.480
就可以了
"currently in your possession for me to act.


430
00:39:07.340 --> 00:39:09.090
假如我去世了
"In case of my own death,


431
00:39:09.100 --> 00:39:13.760
我兒子湯姆將履行我對你的承諾
"my son Thomas will fulfill my promise to you."


432
00:39:14.380 --> 00:39:18.210
對不起 這是你父親的親筆簽名嗎
Forgive me. It's correct signature of your father?


433
00:39:18.220 --> 00:39:19.880
是的
It is.


434
00:39:20.340 --> 00:39:24.330
那我該稱呼你伊薩 還是伊萬
Should I address you then as Issa or Ivan?


435
00:39:24.340 --> 00:39:25.650
伊薩
Issa.


436
00:39:25.660 --> 00:39:28.810
這是我的穆斯林名字 也是我喜歡的
It's my Muslim name and I like.


437
00:39:29.020 --> 00:39:31.840
但這不是你父親給你取的名字？
But not the one your father gave you?


438
00:39:31.980 --> 00:39:34.360
我母親是車臣人
My mother was Chechen.


439
00:39:34.780 --> 00:39:36.410
我希望在你的幫助下
I wish, sir, with your help,


440
00:39:36.420 --> 00:39:39.330
能在漢堡體面的生活
to make an honorable life in Hamburg.


441
00:39:39.340 --> 00:39:41.130
很好
Very good,


442
00:39:41.140 --> 00:39:45.880
但首先 你明白需要有些證明
but first, you understand there are certain questions of fact.


443
00:39:46.780 --> 00:39:50.680
我想問問那個物件
I bring your attention to the matter of the instrument.


444
00:39:56.140 --> 00:40:01.560
我能不能問問 你是怎麼得到的？
May I ask how you came to be in possession of this?


445
00:40:01.980 --> 00:40:04.440
是我父親的律師給我的
It was given to me by my father's lawyer.


446
00:40:05.660 --> 00:40:09.050
那麼說來 是要求我
So it seems I am being asked


447
00:40:09.060 --> 00:40:12.650
履行一個父親對另一個父親的承諾
to fulfill one father's promise to another.


448
00:40:12.660 --> 00:40:15.520
是的 卡爾波夫是我父親
It's true. Karpov was my father.


449
00:40:16.140 --> 00:40:18.320
你們並不親近？
You weren't close?


450
00:40:18.620 --> 00:40:21.120
我父親殺過人
My father was a murderer.


451
00:40:21.220 --> 00:40:23.210
他手上沾有車臣人的鮮血
He has Chechen blood on his hands.


452
00:40:23.220 --> 00:40:26.690
而你似乎願意接受他的錢？
And yet you seem willing enough to take his money?


453
00:40:33.460 --> 00:40:36.770
我聽說你是從土耳其來到這兒的
I understand you came here from Turkey,


454
00:40:37.220 --> 00:40:40.610
是通過非正式的途徑 可以這麼說嗎
by an informal route, shall we say?


455
00:40:41.140 --> 00:40:45.160
我能不能問問 你在土耳其是做什麼的
May I ask, what you were doing in Turkey?


456
00:40:45.780 --> 00:40:47.930
我是在牢裡
I was in prison.


457
00:40:48.460 --> 00:40:50.610
坐牢之前呢
And before that?


458
00:40:52.820 --> 00:40:55.080
在俄國的牢裡
I was in prison in Russia.


459
00:40:56.780 --> 00:40:58.810
-為什麼坐牢  -你不必回答這個問題 伊薩
- Why? - You don't need to answer that, Issa.


460
00:40:58.820 --> 00:41:00.210
為什麼
Why not?


461
00:41:00.220 --> 00:41:01.570
因為這與此無關的
Because it is immaterial.


462
00:41:01.580 --> 00:41:04.080
和什麼無關 裡克特小姐
To what, Fraulein Richter?


463
00:41:04.220 --> 00:41:05.250
你的客戶…
Your client...


464
00:41:05.260 --> 00:41:07.440
他也是你的客戶 布魯先生
He's your client, too, Mr. Brue.


465
00:41:08.060 --> 00:41:09.930
你的客戶要求繼承
Your client lays claim


466
00:41:09.940 --> 00:41:11.610
他父親的賬戶
to his father's account,


467
00:41:11.620 --> 00:41:14.010
可他沒有護照
yet he has no passport,


468
00:41:14.020 --> 00:41:15.770
證明不了自己的身份
cannot prove his identity.


469
00:41:15.780 --> 00:41:19.120
他有鑰匙 也有信 你還想要什麼
He has the key and the letter, what more do you want?


470
00:41:43.060 --> 00:41:46.720
我們聽得不是很清楚 湯姆
We couldn't hear everything so well, Tommy.


471
00:41:47.020 --> 00:41:50.570
賬戶裡有多少錢
So exactly how much are we talking about?


472
00:41:50.880 --> 00:41:52.650
我不能告訴你
I can't tell you.


473
00:41:52.660 --> 00:41:54.240
不能說具數額
Not exactly.


474
00:41:54.740 --> 00:41:57.160
大致數額呢
A ballpark figure?


475
00:41:58.340 --> 00:42:01.450
1萬？ 10萬？ 50萬？

476
00:42:01.460 --> 00:42:04.000
數額
We're talking


477
00:42:04.820 --> 00:42:07.680
在一千萬歐元以上
upwards of 10 million euro.


478
00:42:08.220 --> 00:42:10.000
至少
At least.


479
00:42:19.780 --> 00:42:20.890
-咖啡  -好
- Coffee. - Yes, sir.


480
00:42:20.900 --> 00:42:22.680
-黑咖啡  -馬上就好
- Black. - Right away.


481
00:42:24.140 --> 00:42:25.930
我本不確定你會來
I wasn't sure you'd come.


482
00:42:25.940 --> 00:42:28.200
我想說明一點
I want to make one thing clear.


483
00:42:28.980 --> 00:42:30.680
我不欠你任何人情
I don't owe you anything.


484
00:42:31.860 --> 00:42:34.320
在貝魯特出了什麼事
What happened in Beirut?


485
00:42:35.140 --> 00:42:37.250
你知道在貝魯特出了什麼事
You know what happened in Beirut.


486
00:42:37.260 --> 00:42:39.640
我的聯絡網被毀了
My networks were blown.


487
00:42:40.260 --> 00:42:42.880
那麼調到漢堡是處罰你？
So Hamburg is a punishment?


488
00:42:43.540 --> 00:42:46.720
這要看你是否喜歡漢堡了
Depends on whether you like Hamburg.


489
00:42:48.380 --> 00:42:51.280
或者這是你們的計策
Unless that's what you want people to think?


490
00:42:51.700 --> 00:42:53.410
轉移別人對你的注意力
Take some of the heat off you so you can


491
00:42:53.420 --> 00:42:54.890
你卻暗中進行調查
get on with the real game.


492
00:42:54.900 --> 00:42:56.330
調查什麼
Which is?


493
00:42:56.340 --> 00:42:58.600
費薩爾•阿布杜拉博士
Dr. Faisal Abdullah.


494
00:43:02.460 --> 00:43:06.880
拜託 昆特 我們對他的瞭解 可能和你差不多
Come on, Günther, we probably know as much about him as you do.


495
00:43:09.260 --> 00:43:11.760
你瞭解什麼 馬莎
What do you know, Martha?


496
00:43:14.620 --> 00:43:17.530
我們知道你監視他幾個月了
We know you've been watching him for months,


497
00:43:17.540 --> 00:43:20.770
也知道你受到壓力 需要儘快得出結果
and we know you're under pressure to get results.


498
00:43:21.740 --> 00:43:23.410
我們知道他通過一個
And we know that the man moves money


499
00:43:23.420 --> 00:43:24.730
穆斯林慈善機構來轉移資金
through a network of Muslim charities


500
00:43:24.740 --> 00:43:28.240
每一次轉移 都會有一部分錢失蹤
and every time he does, some of it goes missing.


501
00:43:32.460 --> 00:43:34.330
費薩爾•阿布杜拉博士正是那種
Dr. Faisal Abdullah is everything


502
00:43:34.340 --> 00:43:35.930
我們最喜歡的穆斯林 而且他做的更好
we want him to be and a little bit more.


503
00:43:35.940 --> 00:43:39.640
他寬容、開明 與西方國家交流
He's tolerant, enlightened, engaged with the West.


504
00:43:41.100 --> 00:43:44.960
可每個好人身上 也都有不好的一面 不是嗎
But every good man has a little bit of bad, doesn't he?


505
00:43:48.620 --> 00:43:50.850
在阿布杜拉身上
And in Abdullah's case,


506
00:43:50.860 --> 00:43:52.400
這不好的一面
that little bit


507
00:43:53.860 --> 00:43:55.480
或許就是殺心
just might kill you.


508
00:43:55.780 --> 00:44:00.090
既然你們知道這麼多 他為什麼依然在漢堡自由自在
You know all that, how come he's still walking the streets of Hamburg


509
00:44:00.100 --> 00:44:03.090
而不是被關在關塔那摩監獄裡？
and not rotting in some cell in Guantanamo?


510
00:44:04.380 --> 00:44:06.730
因為我們只是懷疑但沒有證據
Because we think, we don't know.


511
00:44:06.740 --> 00:44:09.810
失蹤的錢 我們不知道去了哪裡
The money leaves and we don't know where it goes.


512
00:44:10.340 --> 00:44:13.970
況且在德國領土上 他還受到德國法律的保護
Anyways, on German soil he's got the protection of German law.


513
00:44:13.980 --> 00:44:16.450
你們可從來不管德國法律
That hasn't stopped you before.


514
00:44:16.460 --> 00:44:18.330
我們不再這麼做了
We don't do that anymore.


515
00:44:18.340 --> 00:44:20.250
那麼是要求我們這麼做了
You want us to do it, then.


516
00:44:20.260 --> 00:44:22.870
我不明白的是 你為何到現在也沒這麼做
I'm more interested in knowing why you haven't done it already?


517
00:44:24.940 --> 00:44:27.600
請在這件事上與我們合作吧 昆特
Please work with us on this one, Günther.


518
00:44:28.820 --> 00:44:30.970
我信不過你們
I don't trust you.


519
00:44:33.220 --> 00:44:35.480
老習慣難改啊
Old habits die hard.


520
00:44:35.780 --> 00:44:38.480
所以信不過你們
That's what I'm worried about.


521
00:44:39.780 --> 00:44:42.320
我說的是你
I was talking about yours.


522
00:44:44.820 --> 00:44:45.970
再見
Have a nice day.


523
00:45:06.420 --> 00:45:08.520
我收到了你的短信
I got your text.


524
00:45:13.940 --> 00:45:15.480
我…
I...


525
00:45:15.900 --> 00:45:18.360
這事我不能幹下去了
I can't do this anymore.


526
00:45:20.180 --> 00:45:23.330
會被人發現的 我能感覺到
Someone's going to find out. I can feel it.


527
00:45:27.460 --> 00:45:29.480
我很害怕
I'm frightened.


528
00:45:33.260 --> 00:45:34.930
他們盯上了我
They are looking at me.


529
00:45:34.940 --> 00:45:36.880
他們都是
All of them.


530
00:45:37.380 --> 00:45:39.680
我不幹了到此為止
I'm done. It's over.


531
00:45:40.460 --> 00:45:43.560
我不是你的間諜 我是學生
I am not your spy. I am a student.


532
00:45:43.900 --> 00:45:45.810
你無法逼我幹這個
